This file contains lecture notes on 'The Mental Process of Note-taking'. The content discusses the importance of listening and thinking in effective note-taking, likening a lecture to a conversation where only one person talks. It emphasizes that good note-taking can be learned, and suggests the reader refer to the Cornell Method of Note-taking (implied in Handout). The notes also highlight the role of questioning in understanding a lecture, as the lecturer tries to anticipate unspoken questions from listeners.

This file is a research paper titled 'AttnLRP: Attention-Aware Layer-wise Relevance Propagation for Transformers'. The authors, Reduan Achtibat, Sayed Mohammad Vakilzadeh Hatefi, Maximilian Dreyer, Aakriti Jain, Thomas Wiegand, Sebastian Lapuschkin, and Wojciech Samek, discuss a method to understand the reasoning process of large language models by extending the Layer-wise Relevance Propagation attribution method to handle attention layers. The goal is to provide faithful attributions for transformer models while maintaining computational efficiency.

This is a PDF guidebook for the 12th Edition of Lonely Planet's travel resource, containing 480 pages. The document provides information on various travel destinations, including must-visit recommendations, sustainable or green recommendations, and locations with no payment required. It also includes symbols for telephone numbers, opening hours, parking, nonsmoking areas, air-conditioning, internet access, Wi-Fi, swimming pools, vegetarian selection, English-language menus, family-friendly locations, pet-friendly locations, buses, ferries, trams, trains, subways, S-Bahn, Skytrain, and metro/MRT stations.

Preprint titled 'An Introduction to String Theory' by Kevin Wray, based on a course taught by Prof. Kostas Skenderis in 2009 at the University of Amsterdam. The document provides an overview and detailed explanation of string theory, including its motivation, types, bosonic string action, classical action for point particles, reparametrization invariance, canonical momenta, and variations of the action.

This PDF file contains a cookbook titled 'FOOD HERO'. The book provides popular recipes with limited ingredients and basic cooking tools, along with suggestions to customize the recipes. It also includes information on refrigerating or freezing leftovers, nutrition facts labels as estimates, and instructions for viewing/sharing recipes online, signing up for Food Hero Monthly emails, and connecting with Food Hero on social media. Additionally, it contains a section about fruit storage and cooking.

Recipe for Chicken Fried Rice from Cooking Classy. The recipe uses brown rice, lean chicken breast, peas and carrots blend, green onions, garlic, eggs, soy sauce, sesame oil, and canola oil. Serves 3 and takes 25 minutes to prepare.

This PDF file contains a travel guide for first-time visitors to Japan, written by a blogger who has a strong affinity for the country. The guide includes a suggested itinerary for 10 days in Japan, with specific recommendations for places to visit and experiences to have. The guide was last updated on February 8, 2025, and has received 22 comments.

This PDF file is a travel guide for the Hawaiian islands, covering topics such as planning your trip, brief history of Hawaii, information about each island (Oahu, Maui, Hawaii - The Big Island, Kauai), Hawaii weather and climate patterns, Hawaii geology and geography. It also includes sections on how to get to Hawaii, money matters, and planning your trip online.
